comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-24T13:02:19.746Z",claude-opus,"Implemented --item-ref-style {auto|label|toon|github} (branch feat/item-ref-style-public-refs). formatItemId now switches on the style: 'label' = neutral (id) never a link (public-doc safe); 'toon' = force .toon blob link (falls back to label without --item-url-base); 'github' = public GitHub issue/PR link derived from the item's gh:owner/repo#N provenance tag (as written by pm-github), falling back to a label when absent/malformed; 'auto' (default) reproduces prior behavior byte-for-byte. CLI + both extension subcommands validate the value with a structured error. 5 generator tests + README docs added; 154/154 tests + changelog:check green."
close_reason: Shipped --item-ref-style (auto|label|toon|github) for public-doc-safe item references.
body: ""
